<!--
Why is / important?

If you write <class ...> (without / at end) → XML thinks more content will come inside → expects a closing </class>.

If you forget to close it → XML parser throws error (well-formedness error).

If you add / at the end (<class .../>) → XML knows this tag is complete in itself → no need for closing tag.

Memory Rule

With children (nested tags inside) → use opening + closing tags (<class> ... </class>).

Without children (empty tag) → use self-closing tag (<class .../>).
-->
